.\" vibe.1 — manual page for vibe-cli
.\" View with:  man ./man/vibe.1
.\"             groff -man -Tutf8 man/vibe.1 | less
.TH VIBE 1 "April 2026" "vibe\-cli" "User Commands"
.
.\" =========================================================
.SH NAME
.\" =========================================================
vibe \- keyboard\-first multi\-project AI coding terminal
.
.\" =========================================================
.SH SYNOPSIS
.\" =========================================================
.B vibe
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR path ]
.RB [ \-\-add
.IR path \|.\|.\|.]
.
.\" =========================================================
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" =========================================================
.B vibe
is a modal, keyboard\-first TUI for running multiple AI coding agents
(Claude, Codex, Cursor, OpenClaw) across many projects simultaneously.
It uses a vim\-like command/prompt/edit modal model, streams live agent
output, manages per\-project memory vaults, and persists sessions across
restarts.
.PP
The interface is divided into panels: a project tab bar at the top, an
agent output stack in the centre, optional side panels (file browser,
editor, memory graph, OpenClaw inbox), an embedded PTY terminal, a
two\-row prompt bar with AI\-generated and user\-defined shortcuts, and
a status bar showing the active agent, permission mode, effort level,
and any session limits.
.
.\" =========================================================
.SH OPTIONS
.\" =========================================================
.TP
.BI \-\-config\  path
Path to the JSON configuration file.
Defaults to
.I config.json
in the current directory.
.TP
.BI \-\-add\  path\ [\fIpath\fR\ ...]
Open one or more project directories on startup.
Paths are added to the project list and the first one becomes active.
.
.\" =========================================================
.SH CONFIGURATION
.\" =========================================================
Configuration is a JSON file.
All keys are optional; the defaults shown below are used when omitted.
.PP
.nf
{
  "agent": {
    "type":   "claude",      // "claude" | "codex" | "cursor" | "openclaw"
    "effort": "medium"       // "low" | "medium" | "high"
  },
  "claude": {
    "permission_mode": "accept_edits"
                             // "plan" | "safe" | "accept_edits" | "bypass"
  },
  "vault": {
    "root": "vault"          // Path to the memory vault directory
  },
  "git": {
    "auto_commit": true,
    "commit_message_prefix": "[VibeCLI] "
  },
  "personalization": {
    "recency_half_life_days":   7.0,
    "decay_interval_hours":    24,
    "project_affinity_weight":  0.4,
    "recency_weight":           0.35,
    "frequency_weight":         0.25
  }
}
.fi
.
.\" =========================================================
.SH MODES
.\" =========================================================
.B vibe
operates in three mutually exclusive input modes.
.TP
.B Command mode
The default mode.
Single\-key shortcuts are active.
Focus rests on the agent panel.
Exit any other mode with
.BR Escape ,
.BR Backspace ,
or
.B ,
(when the prompt is empty).
.TP
.B Prompt mode
Entered by pressing
.B n
or
.BR Enter .
The prompt input receives keyboard focus.
Typing builds a prompt; pressing
.B Enter
submits it to the active agent.
.B Tab
cycles AI\-generated suggestions.
.TP
.B Edit mode
Entered with
.B i
while the editor panel is visible.
The file editor becomes writable.
.B Escape
saves and returns to command mode.
.
